{{For|the Macedonian organisation|Institute of Animal Biotechnology}} {{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox Laboratory |name = National Institute of Animal Biotechnology |motto ="Animal Health for Human Welfare" |logo = |image = |established = 2010 |city = [[Hyderabad, Andhra Pradesh|Hyderabad]], [[India]] |research_field = [[Animal Biotechnology]] |type = |director = Dr. Subeer S. Majumdar |staff = |budget = |operating_agency = [[Department of Biotechnology]] |affiliations = |address = |telephone = |campus = [[Urban area|Urban]], [[Gachibowli]] |website = [http://www.niab.org.in// www.niab.org.in] |footnotes = }}
'''The National Institute of Animal Biotechnology''' <ref>{{cite web|title=NIAB Home page|url=http://www.niab.org.in/}}</ref> is an Indian autonomous research establishment of the [[Department of Biotechnology]],<ref>{{cite web|title=NIAB mandate on DBT Website|url=http://dbtindia.nic.in/uniquepage.asp?id_pk=421|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140429183611/http://dbtindia.nic.in/uniquepage.asp?id_pk=421|archivedate=2014-04-29|df=}}</ref> [[Ministry of Science and Technology (India)]]. The NIAB is being set up in [[Hyderabad, India|Hyderabad]] ([[India]]), under the leadership of Prof. [[Pallu Reddanna]],<ref>{{cite web |title=Prof. Dr. J. Gowrishankar, FNASc, as Officer-on-Special Duty |url=http://www.niab.org.in/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=53&Itemid=55 }}{{dead link|date=February 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> The state of the art Animal Biotechnology and Transgenics institute is housed in the Aryabhata Block of the sprawling [[University of Hyderabad]] in [[Gachibowli]].<ref>[http://www.uohyd.ac.in/index.php/academics/2011-10-27-18-39-44/2011-10-29-17-50-48 National Institute of Animal Biotechnology<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
The primary mandate<ref>{{cite web|title= Mandate and Mission of NIAB|url=http://www.niab.org.in/}}</ref> of NIAB is towards the development of sustainability and globally competitive [[livestock]] ([[farm animals]]) for public and industry through innovative and cutting edge technology. There will emphasis on showing excellence in production of globally competitive [[livestock]] products, [[pharmaceuticals]] (medicines), nutritional products and other biologicals related to animal health care.<ref>[http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-andhrapradesh/article3895433.ece Land from UoH alienated for NIAB - The Hindu<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref>
==Academics and research== The main focus of NIAB will be to nurture the bio-entrepreneurship in the [[animal]] [[biotechnology]] field and to perform hard core [[translational research]] involving [[livestock]] and beneficial to mankind. There will be research laboratories of various disciplines e.g. [[Genomics]], [[Nutrition]] enrichment, [[transgenic]] technology, [[infectious diseases]] and [[Reproductive]] [[biotechnology]]. NIAB will conduct teaching and research programs<ref>{{cite web|title= Academic Programes of NIAB|url= http://www.niab.org.in/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=49&Itemid=56|deadurl= yes|archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20120123123626/http://www.niab.org.in/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=49&Itemid=56|archivedate= 2012-01-23|df= }}</ref> of [[M.Sc.]] and [[Ph.D.]] to train young [[scientist]]s. Dr. Subeer S. Majumdar took charge as new director since 1 August 2016.
